title: Internet erupts as hilarious Marco Rubio job memes circulate online
description: Sky News host James Morrow reacts to the viral internet memes circulating online of US Secretary of State Marco Rubio.  “This week the internet has exploded with memes about Marco Rubio, playing off a long-running joke about the number of jobs he has had to hold at one time in the Trump administration,” Mr Morrow said.   “The internet is imagining a lot of future gigs for Rubio to take on, using AI to imagine Rubio being told about all his new jobs.  “Good luck on your new gigs, Mr Rubio.”

title: Dozens missing and one dead after landfill collapse in the Philippines
description: One person is dead, and dozens are missing after a mountain of rubbish collapsed at a landfill site in the Philippines.  Rescue crews have so far pulled 12 injured people from debris at the site in Cebu City.  Many of the victims are understood to be landfill workers, and as many as 38 people are still missing.  It's not yet known what caused the avalanche.

title: ‘He’s happy to watch America burn’: Tim Walz battered for ‘not standing with law and order’
description: Sky News host Freya Leach says Minnesota Governor Tim Walz has “made Minnesota burn before” for several things, including being “part of the movement to defund the police”.   “During the Black Lives Matter riots, billions of dollars of damage to Minnesota, he did nothing,” Ms Leach said.  “This is a political party, the Democrats, and certainly Tim Walz himself and the Democrats in Minnesota, they do not stand on the side of law and order.  “They are actually happy to watch America burn.”

title: Australia’s guide to healthy eating desperately ‘needs an overhaul’
description: Sky News host Freya Leach has slammed the ‘Australian Guide to Healthy Eating’, claiming it “needs an overhaul”.   “Ours is majority carbs and vegetables,” Ms Leach said.  “I’m okay with some veggies, but that’s way too many carbs.”

title: Plus size trainer broadens market for heavier gym-goers
description: Sky News contributor Jaimee Rogers predicts a plus-size personal trainer has a “good market” for her career and her ability to gain clients.  “I think that this woman has got a huge market for her,” Ms Rogers said.  “If she is getting clients, then good luck to her.”

title: Anthony Albanese clashes with ABC over National Security Commission claim
description: Sky News contributor Kel Richards details how Prime Minister Anthony Albanese took Mike Burgess away from being a permanent member of the National Security Commission in his first term.   “In his first term in office, Albanese took Mike Burgess, who is the head of ASIO, away from being a permanent member of … the National Security Commission,” Mr Richards said.  “Albanese did that … he wasn’t telling the exact truth.”

title: The West’s 'enemies' are buckling worldwide as critics continue to complain about Trump
description: Sky News host James Morrow discusses the monumental geopolitical shakeup occurring internationally.  “You know, all the stuff about how suddenly it is Trump, and not the very nature of humanity, that is causing war and chaos all over the place, two things reveal themselves,” Mr Morrow said.  “One, contrary to all the talk about a new age of dictators and strongmen, freedom is on the move in places where no one had previously dared hope.  “And two, around the globe, the enemies and adversaries of the West are beginning to teeter under the weight of political and economic crises.”

title: Trump is good at ‘precise strikes’ on military targets
description: Broadcaster Kel Richards says US President Donald Trump is good at doing “precise strikes” on military targets.

title: Marco Rubio is a ‘very good’ Secretary of State
description: Broadcaster Kel Richards says US Secretary of State Marco Rubio is “very good” at his role.

title: ‘Reframing the narrative’: Government called out for trying to shift focus onto gun control
description: PR Counsel Managing Director Kristy McSweeney reacts to Prime Minister Anthony Albanese’s delayed decision to call a Royal Commission.   “Of course, there is a significant reframing of the narrative here,” Ms McSweeney told Sky News host James Morrow.   “Don’t forget the government has spent the first 25 days trying to make this issue about gun laws, about gaps in security legislation … everything but antisemitism.”

title: Calls to tighten laws for senior Australian drivers
description: Sky News contributor Jaimee Rogers says there are calls to enforce stricter laws for senior Australian drivers.  Ms Rogers said there is no “problem” with the mandatory eye checks.

title: Mexico is ‘run by cartels’ for the most part
description: Sky News host Freya Leach says Mexico is being “run by cartels” for the most part.

title: Mandatory eye checks for senior drivers shouldn’t be a ‘controversial’ rule
description: Sky News contributor Jaimee Rogers says a mandatory eye check for senior drivers shouldn’t be a “controversial” rule.

title: Mexico doesn’t have ‘control’ over much of the country
description: Sky News host Freya Leach says Mexico does not have “control” over much of its own country.

title: Donald Trump talks about ‘land strikes’ in Mexico
description: Sky News host Freya Leach says US President Donald Trump is now talking about “land strikes” in Mexico.
